&lt;p&gt;Also, &lt;span class=&quot;math-tex&quot;&gt;\({\rm{n\;}} = {\rm{\;}}\frac{4}{{\rm{p}}}{\rm{\;}} = {\rm{\;}}\frac{4}{{\frac{1}{4}}}{\rm{\;}} = {\rm{\;}}16\)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
Now, &lt;span class=&quot;math-tex&quot;&gt;\(\left( {{\rm{n}} + 1} \right){\rm{p\;}} = {\rm{\;}}\left( {16 + 1} \right)\frac{1}{4}{\rm{\;}} = {\rm{\;}}\frac{{17}}{4}{\rm{\;}} = {\rm{\;}}4 + \frac{1}{4}\)&lt;/span&gt;

