&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;math-tex&quot;&gt;\(\rm mean = \frac{{1 + 2 + 3 + \ldots \cdots \cdots + 10}}{{10}} = 5.5\)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Given, P(X &amp;le;&amp;nbsp;4) =&amp;nbsp;&lt;span class=&quot;math-tex&quot;&gt;\(\frac{{1}}{{5}}\)&lt;/span&gt;, From symmetricity of&amp;nbsp;distribution, P(X&amp;nbsp;&amp;ge; 7) =&amp;nbsp;&lt;span class=&quot;math-tex&quot;&gt;\(\frac{{1}}{{5}}\)&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;we know that total probability is equal to one hence&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;math-tex&quot;&gt;\(\rm P(-\infty &amp;lt; x ≤ 4) + P(4 &amp;lt; x &amp;lt; 7) + P(7 ≤ x ≤ \infty) = 1\)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;math-tex&quot;&gt;\(\rm \begin{array}{l} \Rightarrow \frac{1}{5} + P\left( {4 &amp;lt; x &amp;lt; 7} \right) + \frac{1}{5} = 1\\ \rm P\left( {4 &amp;lt; x &amp;lt; 7} \right) = 1 - \frac{2}{5} = \frac{3}{5} \end{array}\)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

